    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure I completely understand the usage case with the `RangeInput` widget. \r\n\r\nFrom what I understood you want to display a list of languages `A-E F-J K-O P-T U-Z` where you can click on to apply a filter. To do this you have to put the language as an [`attributeForFaceting`](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/api-parameters/attributesForFaceting/) inside the index. Then in the front end you can now use this attribute with a [`refinementList`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html). It displays the list of the available languages. Here is [an example](https://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/create-instantsearch-app/tree/templates/instantsearch.js) with a list of brand but you got the ideas.",
